HEADWORD: Tiercelet
<hw>Tierce"let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>tercel</ets>, <ets>tercelet</ets>,
F. <ets>tiercelet</ets>, a dim. of (assumed) <ets>tiercel</ets>, or LL.
<ets>tertiolus</ets>, dim. fr. L. <ets>tertius</ets> the third; -- so
called, according to some, because every third bird in the nest is a
male, or, according to others, because the male is the third part less
than female. Cf. <er>Tercel</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Falconry)</fld> <def>The
male of various falcons, esp. of the peregrine; also, the male of the
goshawk.</def> <rj><au>Encyc. Brit.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

